This paper describes a classifier that uses unsupervised distributional measures to discriminate between semantically related and unrelated words and classify related pairs according to their semantic relation. This involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the computer science sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computation and language (cs.CC). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
